âFor Grisha?â said the little girl, pointing to the chocolate.

âYes, yes.â And still stroking her little shoulder, he kissed her on
the roots of her hair and neck, and let her go.

âThe carriage is ready,â said Matvey; âbut thereâs someone to see you
with a petition.â

âBeen here long?â asked Stepan Arkadyevitch.

âHalf an hour.â

âHow many times have I told you to tell me at once?â

âOne must let you drink your coffee in peace, at least,â said Matvey,
in the affectionately gruff tone with which it was impossible to be
