ââinstant of passion?â he said, and would have gone on, but at that
word, as at a pang of physical pain, her lips stiffened again, and
again the muscles of her right cheek worked.

âGo away, go out of the room!â she shrieked still more shrilly, âand
donât talk to me of your passion and your loathsomeness.â

She tried to go out, but tottered, and clung to the back of a chair to
