an honest man, you cannot help caring about it and sympathizing with
the movement, and so wishing to work for it.â

âBut I still do not admit this movement to be just,â said Konstantin
Levin, reddening a little.

âWhat! But you said just now....â

âThatâs to say, I donât admit itâs being either good or possible.â

âThat you canât tell without making the trial.â

âWell, supposing thatâs so,â said Levin, though he did not suppose so
