or is it not God?â and the unity of the impression is destroyed.â

âWhy so? I think that for educated people,â said Mihailov, âthe
question cannot exist.â

Golenishtchev did not agree with this, and confounded Mihailov by his
support of his first idea of the unity of the impression being
